2011-06-01T05:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/s-korea-to-start-buying-savings-banks-bad-loans-in-june.html
South Korea  plans in June to start
buying bad loans extended by savings banks to finance
construction projects, the Financial Services Commission said
today in an e-mailed statement. State-run Korea Asset Management
Corp. plans to use at least 3.5 trillion won to buy the so-
called project financing loans, the statement said.  South Korea will also tighten regulations on the issuance of
subordinated bonds by savings banks, the financial regulator
said in a separate statement.  -- Editor: Shinhye Kang, Gearoid Reidy  To contact the reporter on this story:
